text: Mata'afa George Keenan (born Rarotonga, 26 October 1960) is a Cook Islands- born Samoan former rugby union player. He played as a lock. ==Career== Keenan debuted in the 1991 Rugby World Cup roster in the match against Wales, at Cardiff on 6 October 1991. His last international match was against Australia at Sydney, on 6 August 1994. ==Notes== ==References== *Mat Keenan International Statistics *Mata'afa G.
